tspan.tspan: Chrome Extension that allows user to lock table rows to
prevent data entry. The extension can be enabled or disabled on a per
domain basic. State is saved and restored on returned visits.
This script monitors the active tab and determines if the extension
should be enabled or disabled and updates the browserAction icon, tooltip and
context menus to match saved state. The default state is to be disabled on new
domains. The user can enable the extension via the browserAction context menu.
Update browserAction view (icon, tooltip, badge) to match enabled/disabled state.
Update browserAction contextMenu to match enabled/disabled state.
OnEnable inject ‘tableRowLocker.js’ into content script sandbox.
This script handles all of the web page view manipulation
and state changes by monitoring the extension storage
Detecting all <TR> elements on the page.
Attaching lock element to each row with click event
Syncing lock state with extension storage
onClickEvent set update extension storage to match
